[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_t6v10")
reagent_id = "CaCO3"
title = "Calcium carbonate"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CaCO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]100 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
Ca + H₂CO₃ → CaCO₃ + H₂  
Ca(OH)₂ + CO₂ → CaCO₃ + H₂O  
Ca(OH)₂ + H₂CO₃ → CaCO₃ + 2H₂O  
CaO + H₂CO₃ → CaCO₃ + H₂O  
CaO + CO₂ → CaCO₃
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of calcium and carbonate ions.  
• Slightly soluble in water.  
• Reacts with acids to produce carbon dioxide.
[b]Where calcium carbonate is found[/b]
• In limestone, chalk, and marble.  
• In shells of marine organisms.  
• In eggshells.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of cement and lime.  
• Used as a building material.  
• Used in agriculture to reduce soil acidity.
[b]Safety[/b]
Generally safe, but dust can irritate the lungs if inhaled."
